Auto-Install Requests

Monitor and interact with auto-install requests on the Requests tab.

Each auto-install request includes:
Name
Type (App Create, App Update, App Delete, or Start Dataflow)
Status (Success, Failed, In Progress, Not Started, or Canceled)
Reason (failed reason for failed requests)
Created By
Created On
App

Request Actions:

Open—Opens the associated installed app details.
Delete App—Deletes the installed app.
View Log—Displays the auto-install request log.
Try Again—Runs the auto-install request for this installed app again.
Cancel—Appears only when the auto-install request status is In Progress.

Clean Stale Requests:
Click to clean the list of auto-install requests of stale requests.

Search and Filter Requests:
Use search bar or filter dropdown list to search and filter auto-install request list.

View Auto Request Details:
After opening the auto-install request details, see the Details view which includes:
Request name
Creation date and user
Last modification date and user
Request status
